extends layout-tour

block view
    .content.doc-page.clearfix.prelude-content(ng-controller="TourCtrl").
        <div class="clearfix">
            <div class="docs col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-8">
                <h2>Tour: Planning ahead</h2>
                <p>Circle Blvd was made to help you adapt as your priorities change over time.</p>

                <div class="row choice-menu">
                    <div class="col-xs-4 choice">
                        <a href="/tour"><div class="circle-menu">
                            <div class="text">Start</div>
                        </div></a>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-xs-4 choice">
                        <a href="/tour/work"><div class="circle-menu">
                            <div class="text">Work</div>
                        </div></a>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-xs-4 choice active">
                        <div class="circle-menu">
                            <div class="text">Plan</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p>Plan for the short term and the long term. Make something great.</p>

                <div class="row choice-menu">
                    <div class="col-xs-4 choice plan-choice" ng-class="{active: isShowing('tags')}">
                        <a class="jsLink" ng-click="show('tags')"><div class="plan-menu">
                            <i class="glyphicon">#</i>
                            <div class="text">Tags</div>
                        </div></a>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-xs-4 choice plan-choice" ng-class="{active: isShowing('bump')}">
                        <a class="jsLink" ng-click="show('bump')"><div class="plan-menu">
                            <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-up"></i>
                            <div class="text">What's Next</div>
                        </div></a>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-xs-4 choice plan-choice" ng-class="{active: isShowing('roadmap')}">
                        <a class="jsLink" ng-click="show('roadmap')"><div class="plan-menu">
                            <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-road"></i>
                            <div class="text">Roadmap</div>
                        </div></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>


        <div ng-cloak ng-if="isShowing('tags')">
            <div class="docs col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-8">
                <p>Use <strong>#hashtags</strong> in task summaries to label them as you see fit, 
                and then filter on those tags. In this example, two tasks are
                tagged with #Grocery.</p> 
            </div>

            <sp-story-list 
                data="tags" 
                mindset="'detailed'"
                account-name="whoami"
                owners="['Alaina', 'Nicholas', 'Phil', whoami]" 
                keyboard="keyboard"
                mouse="mouse"
                is-facade="isFacade"></sp-story-list>

            <div class="docs col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-8">
                <!-- <p class="after-list">After!</p> -->
            </div>
        </div>


        <div ng-cloak ng-if="isShowing('bump')">
            <div class="docs col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-8">
                <p>At the end of a work session or meeting, you might scan your list for what's next. Use the <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-up"></i> icon for this mindset.</p> 
            </div>

            <sp-story-list 
                data="bump" 
                mindset="'bump'"
                account-name="whoami"
                owners="['Alaina', 'Nicholas', 'Phil', whoami]" 
                keyboard="keyboard"
                mouse="mouse"
                is-facade="isFacade"></sp-story-list>

            <div class="docs col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-8">
                <p class="after-list">Notice the <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i> icon is still on tasks above the black task, for minor adjustments as you go.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div ng-cloak ng-if="isShowing('roadmap')">
            <div class="hidden-xs">
                <sp-story-list 
                    data="roadmap"
                    mindset="'roadmap'" 
                    account-name="whoami"
                    owners="['Alaina', 'Nicholas', 'Phil', whoami]" 
                    keyboard="keyboard"
                    mouse="mouse"
                    is-facade="isFacade"></sp-story-list>
            </div>
            <div class="visible-xs">
                <p>(The roadmap mindset has a lot going on, and it's only visible on larger screens.)</p>
            </div>

            <div class="docs col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-8">
                <p class="after-list">With the <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-road"></i> mindset,
                you can move tasks great distances within your list very quickly. This is just a
                small demonstration, but we think you'll get the idea.</p>

                <p>Use the <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i> icon to 
                move tasks from the left column to the right. With a longer list, selecting the 
                mileposts on the right will scroll to where they are in the left column.</p>
            </div>
        </div>